CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

com/repos/web-platform-tests/wpt","watchers":2411,"watchers_count":2411},"sha":"a06709fbf13b28f4b1b3d24f5bbc2e5274fe87af","user":{"avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/37226233?v=4","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/events{/privacy}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/gists{/gist_id}","gravatar_id":"","html_url":"https://github.com/web-platform-tests","id":37226233,"login":"web-platform-tests","node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjM3MjI2MjMz","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/repos","site_admin":false,"starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/subscriptions","type":"Organization","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests"}},"body":"Previously CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

set -ex; echo "infrastructure/ tests"; ~/start.sh https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt.git refs/pull/18403/merge; cd ~/web-platform-tests; sudo apt update -qqy; sudo apt install -qqy libnss3-tools libappindicator1 fonts-liberation; ./tools/ci/run_tc.py \
  --oom-killer \
  --browser=firefox \
  --browser=chrome \
  --channel=experimental \
  --no-hosts \
  --xvfb \
  wptrunner_infrastructure \
  tools/ci/ci_wptrunner_infrastructure.sh;

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

com/repos/web-platform-tests/wpt","watchers":2411,"watchers_count":2411},"sha":"a06709fbf13b28f4b1b3d24f5bbc2e5274fe87af","user":{"avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/37226233?v=4","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/events{/privacy}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/gists{/gist_id}","gravatar_id":"","html_url":"https://github.com/web-platform-tests","id":37226233,"login":"web-platform-tests","node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjM3MjI2MjMz","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/repos","site_admin":false,"starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/subscriptions","type":"Organization","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests"}},"body":"Previously CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

com/repos/web-platform-tests/wpt","watchers":2411,"watchers_count":2411},"sha":"a06709fbf13b28f4b1b3d24f5bbc2e5274fe87af","user":{"avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/37226233?v=4","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/events{/privacy}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/gists{/gist_id}","gravatar_id":"","html_url":"https://github.com/web-platform-tests","id":37226233,"login":"web-platform-tests","node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjM3MjI2MjMz","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/repos","site_admin":false,"starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/subscriptions","type":"Organization","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests"}},"body":"Previously CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.

com/repos/web-platform-tests/wpt","watchers":2411,"watchers_count":2411},"sha":"a06709fbf13b28f4b1b3d24f5bbc2e5274fe87af","user":{"avatar_url":"https://avatars0.githubusercontent.com/u/37226233?v=4","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/events{/privacy}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/gists{/gist_id}","gravatar_id":"","html_url":"https://github.com/web-platform-tests","id":37226233,"login":"web-platform-tests","node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjM3MjI2MjMz","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/repos","site_admin":false,"starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests/subscriptions","type":"Organization","url":"https://api.github.com/users/web-platform-tests"}},"body":"Previously CSSTransformNonInterpolableValue assumed that anything that was
composited on-top of would be single. However that is not true; in the simple
case where there is a replace animation before it, the replace effect will be a
pair:

target.animate({ transform: [ 'scale(1)', 'scale(2)' ] }, 1000);
target.animate({ transform: [ 'rotate(0)', 'rotate(90deg)' ] },
               { duration: 1000, composite: 'add' });

In the example above, the scale animation would not yet have been reduced to a
single interpolated value, so the DCHECK for is_single_ would fail. This CL
fixes the logic to perform an interpolation in that case.
